Welcome to the=C2=A0205=C2=A0newly Not Boring people=C2=A0who have joined u=
s since last Tuesday! If you haven=E2=80=99t subscribed, join=C2=A0212,148 =
smart, curious folks by subscribing here:
Today=E2=80=99s Not Boring is brought to you by=E2=80=A6 Mercury [ https://=
substack.com/redirect/ecd0e634-c36a-4540-b038-da66b811c89d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAw=
Z3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ]
Mercury is banking engineered for startups. But they go beyond banking, pro=
viding the resources and connections startups need to become success storie=
s. We=E2=80=99ve used Mercury at Not Boring since day 1=E2=80=A6and frankly=
, it=E2=80=99s very rare I see a startup that doesn=E2=80=99t. The company =
just launched Mercury Raise [ https://substack.com/redirect/ecd0e634-c36a-4=
540-b038-da66b811c89d?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOs=
a8-6m8ExkRNpU ]: a comprehensive founder success platform built to remove r=
oadblocks at every step of the startup journey.=C2=A0
Access: Get exclusive intros from Mercury to investors, experts, and other =
founders.
Fundraising: Submit your deck and get in front of hundreds of active invest=
ors looking to invest in companies like yours.
Community: Attend unfiltered conversations with industry vets and build rel=
ationships with other founders at similar stages.=20
Navigating this whole startup thing can be hard and lonely =E2=80=93 but wi=
th Mercury Raise you don=E2=80=99t have to go it alone.
Hi friends =F0=9F=91=8B,
Happy Tuesday! Fun one today.=C2=A0
After starting its life as a controversial company for supporting the US mi=
litary, Anduril has been proven prescient by the war in Ukraine, the growin=
g threat of China, and its early ability to win contracts from the US and a=
llied militaries.=20
As a result, the company=E2=80=99s story has been told in numerous newslett=
ers, publications, and podcasts.=C2=A0I=E2=80=99ll put the links at the end=
, and I highly recommend reading and listening to any or all of them for th=
e full Anduril story. But for today=E2=80=99s essay, I wanted to focus on o=
ne piece specifically: Anduril=E2=80=99s acquisitions.=C2=A0
Just six years old, Anduril has made a splash with five acquisitions since =
2021. I wanted to understand why, and how, they do it. In the process, I le=
arned a ton about the future of defense, Anduril=E2=80=99s ambitions to con=
nect the old way of doing things with the new, and what it takes to build a=
 generational Hard Startup.=20
Full disclosure: I=E2=80=99m an investor in Anduril through an SPV we put t=
ogether for Not Boring Capital=E2=80=99s LPs, and a big fan of the company,=
 but this isn=E2=80=99t a sponsored deep dive. After their most recent acqu=
isition, I asked them to tell me about their M&A strategy, and I=E2=80=99m =
excited to share what I learned with you.=20
Let=E2=80=99s get to it.
Anduril: Acquiring Prime
The best way to think about Anduril [ https://substack.com/redirect/75ea523=
d-6018-4a0a-954f-cb29f191870a?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlX=
XepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ] is through the series of nested bets the company is=
 making.=C2=A0
Bet #1: The way humans fight wars, or more importantly deter each other fro=
m fighting wars in the first place, is changing: from large, expensive, exq=
uisite hardware platforms to distributed systems of smaller, cheaper, more =
networked defense products.
Bet #2: The United States Department of Defense (DoD) and its allies will b=
e able to transition the way it buys capabilities to account for this new r=
eality: from the DoD=E2=80=99s slow Planning, Programming, Budgeting, and E=
xecution (PPBE) system to what Anduril Chief Strategy Officer Christian Bro=
se calls a =E2=80=9CMoneyball Military [ https://substack.com/redirect/415b=
2910-923b-4dc2-8a39-4dccf1439cf0?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZj=
mlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].=E2=80=9D
Bet #3: No incumbent in technology or defense is able to serve this new nee=
d: large technology companies that have the software chops have been incent=
ivized to keep China happy and have shied away from defense, and the Defens=
e Primes =E2=80=93 the five leading contractors that provide major military=
 systems, platforms, and services to the DOD =E2=80=93 don=E2=80=99t have t=
he software chops, the ability to recruit the people who do, or the incenti=
ve to move away from the cost-plus gravy-train.=C2=A0
Bet #4: By investing in software R&D upfront, it will be able to better del=
iver the capabilities the DoD needs to fight the new kind of war, more chea=
ply: that its Lattice OS [ https://substack.com/redirect/37c12abc-13a7-46a7=
-83ed-7cd0526bda08?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-=
6m8ExkRNpU ] will let Anduril deliver more capable hardware products for le=
ss money, and that its advantages will compound with each new product it pl=
ugs in.=C2=A0
Bet #5: Startups can develop the advanced technologies that DoD will need b=
etter than incumbents, and that Anduril can sell them into DoD better than =
the startups building them can: that it can serve as a pipe between the com=
petitive capitalism of the startup and SMB defense tech ecosystem and the m=
ore centrally-planned DoD acquisition machine.=C2=A0
Bet #6: This one is actually a series of bets Anduril makes every time it b=
uilds a new product, or acquires a company that does: that it will be able =
to sell that particular product into DoD and ultimately into large programs=
=2E
The first three bets define the battlefield on which Anduril is fighting, a=
nd the second three define the company=E2=80=99s battle plan.=C2=A0
Anduril, founded in 2017, doesn=E2=80=99t look like either a typical tech s=
tartup or a traditional defense contractor. It was born to fill the gap bet=
ween the two worlds. Its mission is =E2=80=9Ctransforming US & allied milit=
ary capabilities with advanced technology.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0
The way I=E2=80=99ve come to think about the company is as a meta-version o=
f Lattice.=C2=A0
Lattice is Anduril=E2=80=99s software operating system. It serves as an int=
egration layer between legacy defense systems, modern sensors and weapons, =
and Anduril=E2=80=99s own hardware, giving operators the ability to make fa=
ster, better-informed decisions.=C2=A0
Similarly, Anduril the company aims to serve as an integration layer betwee=
n old and new, between the traditional, centrally-planned way the DoD procu=
