Prime Time
Anduril is a Russian doll fighting to help America=E2=80=99s defense indust=
ry plan in a less Soviet way.=C2=A0
The company is making a series of nested bets on the future of war and the =
role it can play in bringing it about. The DoD needs to shift to distribute=
d systems of smaller, cheaper, more networked defense products, and Anduril=
 is betting that it can serve as the Lattice-like integration layer between=
 the DoD=E2=80=99s centrally-planned PPBE system and the free market of sta=
rtups and SMBs that produce the advanced technology it needs.=C2=A0
To do so, its building and acquiring technologies to take advantage of open=
 windows during which it might be able to sell those technologies, coupled =
with Lattice, into large programs. Those windows exist within a larger wind=
ow: the period in which Anduril is the only logical buyer for the technolog=
ies it believes will make the difference in the conflicts to come. For now,=
 it=E2=80=99s brilliantly counter-positioned against the incumbent Primes.=
=C2=A0
Five times in the past two and a half years, this has meant acquiring compa=
nies in order to speed their time to market. My hunch is that we=E2=80=99ll=
 see Anduril lean even harder into acquisitions versus in-house development=
 in the years to come, for a couple of reasons:
Bet on the Power of Free Markets. If one of Anduril=E2=80=99s key bets is t=
hat the market will produce ideas, technologies, and capabilities that bett=
er respond to the military=E2=80=99s needs than a centrally-planned system,=
 then I suspect that bet extends to Anduril itself. Instead of planning far=
 enough in advance to develop each technology in-house, it can let the mark=
et do its thing, and then pick the winners in that sweet spot when Anduril =
can be early with an educated view towards near-term DoD demand.=C2=A0
Differentiation. A lot of companies make hardware; no one has built the com=
bination of software and DoD trust that Anduril has. By focusing on buildin=
g out that integration layer, it can remain the buyer-of-choice for the mos=
t innovative defense tech companies while becoming the DoD=E2=80=99s partne=
r-of-choice for advanced technologies that work with the rest of its assets=
=2E=C2=A0
Of course, the situation is fluid and things will change. Primes might appr=
eciate the threat and begin competing for the companies Anduril wants to ac=
quire. The DoD itself might listen to Brose and begin buying large quantiti=
es of attritable, consumable, autonomous hardware directly, lessening the n=
eed for Anduril to acquire those companies.=C2=A0
In that case, Anduril will adapt. The more I learn, the more I think viewin=
g Anduril as a meta-version of its products is useful. Just as its products=
 enable operators to close the kill chain by understanding, deciding, and a=
cting more quickly, Anduril itself can be defined by this continuous proces=
s of understanding, deciding, and acting.=C2=A0
What=E2=80=99s brilliant about Anduril=E2=80=99s acquisitions to me isn=E2=
=80=99t necessarily any of the specific companies they=E2=80=99ve acquired,=
 but how cohesively its M&A strategy fits with the realities of its current=
 position and future ambitions:
Vision-Aligned Acquisitions: Anduril aims to acquire startups and SMBs that=
 align with its vision of future warfare, particularly those with advanced =
technologies that can be integrated into its existing Lattice platform.
Private Funding Flexibility: Leveraging its $2.3 billion in private venture=
 capital, Anduril can make high-risk bets in acquisitions without immediate=
 justification to public shareholders, giving it an edge over public Defens=
e Primes.
Plug Acquisitions into a Platform: Anduril has spent years building Anduril=
 OS =E2=80=93 the combination of software and trust with DoD =E2=80=93 whic=
h makes it an attractive and effective acquirer.=C2=A0
Early-Mover Advantage: By acquiring companies early in their lifecycle, And=
uril gets to shape both the requirements and the narrative surrounding new =
defense technologies, making itself indispensable to its customers.
Balance Vision with Near-Term Market Demands: =E2=80=9CIs it urgent and can=
 we solve it in five years?=E2=80=9D puts practical constraints around earl=
y bets. Being too early is the same as being wrong.=C2=A0
Race Against Time: The company is on a clock to prove its financial model a=
nd scale up before the larger Defense Primes adapt and start competing for =
the same advanced technology companies.
Normally, a writer might frame that list as =E2=80=9C6 M&A tricks you can l=
earn from Anduril,=E2=80=9D but the takeaway for other startups shouldn=E2=
=80=99t be, =E2=80=9CDo M&A like Anduril does.=E2=80=9D It should be, =E2=
=80=9CDo strategy like Anduril does.=E2=80=9D If you really want to build a=
 generational company, strategy really matters [ https://substack.com/redir=
ect/da92f1bf-fd1d-46dc-a96e-b3981dec28cc?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_=
ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ].
Anduril is a singular company, and its strategy works because the company=
=E2=80=99s leaders have crafted it for the specific mission at-hand. That s=
houldn=E2=80=99t be a surprise. Richard Rummelt=E2=80=99s strategy kernel -=
 diagnosis, guiding policy, coherent actions =E2=80=93 is essentially a lon=
ger-range version of the kill chain =E2=80=93 understand, decide, act. No s=
tartup I=E2=80=99ve encountered has been more clear-eyed and thorough in it=
s diagnosis, or followed it through more fully into a guiding policy and co=
herent actions than Anduril has.=C2=A0
Instead of building a large, hard-to-turn, exquisite platform, Anduril has =
chosen to build its company as a network that=E2=80=99s constantly taking i=
n new information and using it to adjust in real-time.=C2=A0
That=E2=80=99s why, even as the Primes begin to move to where Anduril is to=
day, I expect that the company will be able to respond more quickly to the =
changing defense landscape of the future.=C2=A0
So will Anduril become the sixth Prime?=C2=A0
Steckman doesn=E2=80=99t think they=E2=80=99re quite there yet, but he beli=
eves they=E2=80=99re getting close. They=E2=80=99re finally getting invited=
 to sit next to the Primes at big events, getting mentioned in the same bre=
ath as those century-old stalwarts. 2024, he thinks, is going to be a big y=
ear:=C2=A0
If we stick to what we=E2=80=99re good at =E2=80=94 high levels of control =
and autonomy, unmanned systems, core technology areas =E2=80=93 it will end=
 up working out. If you look at the Defense budget over the next ten years,=
 the sliding bar is moving into favor. If we stay the course, the addressab=
le market increases beneath us.
On the meta level, that=E2=80=99s the real benefit of being early and nimbl=
e. Anduril has been able to position the company for where it believes the =
market will be in ten years. It=E2=80=99s doing things that are hard for pu=
blic Primes to do =E2=80=93 investing in software R&D upfront, acquiring co=
mpanies before they=E2=80=99re generating meaningful EBITDA, taking risk on=
 new products instead of banking on the certainty of cost-plus =E2=80=93 th=
at position it for what=E2=80=99s to come.=C2=A0
If Anduril does become a Prime, it won=E2=80=99t look like the other five. =
It doesn=E2=80=99t plan to build exquisite platforms like manned fighter je=
ts or multi-billion-dollar aircraft carriers. It realizes that fighting the=
 adversary on their own terms is a losing strategy.=C2=A0
When I asked what was next on the shopping list, they told me they=E2=80=99=
re looking at space. If they go up there, I would imagine their products lo=
ok more like swarms of cheap, smart, distributed systems, like Array Labs [=
 https://substack.com/redirect/6990beef-3998-4ea9-8a19-20b25bc12f2d?j=3DeyJ=
1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU ], than the mul=
ti-hundred-million-dollar satellites the government and Primes have traditi=
onally built. The future Anduril envisions will be distributed and connecte=
d by software.=C2=A0
Breaking into a massive industry dominated by powerful incumbents and chang=
ing it from the inside requires making risky bets against a clear vision of=
 the way things should and will be, and adjusting as new information and op=
portunities arise. I=E2=80=99m betting that Anduril will pull it off.=C2=A0
