ll modern technology into DoD&#8221; playbook.</span></p><p style=3D"color:=
 rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">=
If Anduril can continue to build trust with the DoD, acquire companies with=
 the right capabilities at the right time, and sell them into increasingly =
large programs, it has the chance to inject some capitalism to the nation&#=
8217;s fight against our centrally-planned adversaries, and become a Prime =
in its own right.&#160;</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 1=
6px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">We&#8217;ll dive (pun intended=
) into the details of specific transactions, but to understand why Anduril =
acquires companies, we need to start by understanding the defense market.&#=
160;</p><h3 class=3D"header-with-anchor-widget" style=3D"-moz-appearance: o=
